-- LPL Financial profit falls 4.4 pct as costs rise
-- By Amrutha Gayathri in Bangalore
-- Wed Jul 30, 2014 06:19AM EDT
-- None



July 30 (Reuters) - LPL Financial Holdings Inc <LPLA.O>, one of the five biggest U.S. broker-dealers, reported a 4.4 percent drop in quarterly profit, as restructuring and other expenses increased.

Net income fell to $43.1 million, or 42 cents per share, from $45.1 million, or 42 cents per share, a year earlier. The company reported adjusted earnings per share of 61 cents for the second quarter ended June 30.